Head (
Figure 6A
) brown between antennae, clypeus and labrum. Clypeus and labrum covered with numerous short, thin setae. Frons convex moderately, with scales between antennae and ocelli.

Antennae shorter than body length, antennae length/body length about 0.70. Scapus and pedicellus of antennae densely scaled, flagellum not scaled. Scapus rather long (length/width about 2.0); pedicellus as long as wide. Flagellum uniformly lightbrownish, junctions between segments pale. Divisions number of flagellum maximum observed 24 divisions, proximal 10 divisions not annulated, divisions 11–15 annulated into three to six annuli, divisions 16–26 with seven to nine annuli. The distal chains with eight or nine annuli, each one about thrice as wide as long (
Figure 6B
).

Head (
Figure 6K
) as in male. More setae present in the labrum and the clypeus. Compound eyes as in the male, the contact line/length: 0.50–0.52; length/width: 0.84. Paired ocelli shoe-shaped, red brownish (in alcohol), the width of ocellus slightly narrower than that of compound eye (width of ocellus about 0.74–0.76 of that of compound eye).

Antennae as in male. Antennae length/body length about 0.70. Scapus rather long (length/width about 2.00). Division number of flagellum maximum observed 26. Proximal 10 divisions not annulated, divisions 11–14 annulated into three to four annuli, divisions 15–24 with six to seven annuli. The distal chains with seven or eight annuli, which are about as long as wide (
Figure 6L
). The distal chains with sensilla and thin sensorial points.

Labial palp (
Figure 6M
) as in male.
